    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2879518805?book_show_action=true">Jul 01, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="James Tingle" class="user" itemprop="url" name="James Tingle" href="/user/show/66386578-james-tingle">James Tingle</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2879518805" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1375172150851495857"><br/>I started another of Bellow&apos;s novels, Herzog, years ago at Uni and gave up about one third through it as it all felt a bit slow and ponderous and although fairly well written, didn&apos;t grab me enough really. Maybe I&apos;ll give that one another go some time but with Seize the Day, I did manage to finish it at least, but it seemed hard work, especially as it&apos;s such a short book. Bellow seems to be quite a long winded chap and likes to say something over the stretch of a page that could be summed up in </span>
  <span id="freeText1375172150851495857" style="display:none"><br />I started another of Bellow's novels, Herzog, years ago at Uni and gave up about one third through it as it all felt a bit slow and ponderous and although fairly well written, didn't grab me enough really. Maybe I'll give that one another go some time but with Seize the Day, I did manage to finish it at least, but it seemed hard work, especially as it's such a short book. Bellow seems to be quite a long winded chap and likes to say something over the stretch of a page that could be summed up in a few sentences...fair enough if that's his way of writing I suppose, but I struggled to keep my interest going at times.<br />The plot is pretty minimal although that can really work with certain novels if the protagonist is particularly interesting- unfortunately, this guy was a bit of a grey man, a bit of a background player who slipped into the limelight by accident it almost felt like. The whole living with his Dad in the hotel thing was quite a nice idea, but not much seemed to come of that scenario and so that all fell flat as well...the two stars are really for the writing standard which I suppose was fair enough in places, but I'm not sure I'll be devouring the whole of Bellow's back catalog any time soon. I have a copy of Henderson the Rain King somewhere so might try that one day if I feel up to the task!</span>
  <a data-text-id="1375172150851495857" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


