<span id="freeTextContainer1744637122377691791">The little novella ‘Seize the Day’ is rightly called a masterpiece. <br/>Like a modern Greek tragedy, we have in Tommy Wilhelm a protagonist who is facing the world closing in on him. Instead of shutting down, giving in or giving up, he feels very deeply. What he ask for is just a bare minimum of human understanding, of compassion<br/><br/>Sadly, his father, who is fiercely aloof, can’t provide this and regards him as a loser. He ex-wife demands even more alimony. He is swindled out of the little cash he has b</span>
  <span id="freeText1744637122377691791" style="display:none">The little novella ‘Seize the Day’ is rightly called a masterpiece. <br />Like a modern Greek tragedy, we have in Tommy Wilhelm a protagonist who is facing the world closing in on him. Instead of shutting down, giving in or giving up, he feels very deeply. What he ask for is just a bare minimum of human understanding, of compassion<br /><br />Sadly, his father, who is fiercely aloof, can’t provide this and regards him as a loser. He ex-wife demands even more alimony. He is swindled out of the little cash he has by a fast talking merchant of success.<br /><br />Having nowhere to turn, he absentmindedly joins a funeral possession, and upon seeing the body in the coffin, breaks down sobbing for all of us. A memorable conclusion. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="1744637122377691791" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

